SIMPLE: anxiety
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anxiety
<hw>Anx*i"e*ty</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Anxieties</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>anxietas</ets>,
fr. <ets>anxius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>anxi⟦eacute⟧t⟦eacute⟧</ets>. See
<er>Anxious</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Concern or solicitude
respecting some thing or event, future or uncertain, which disturbs the
mind, and keeps it in a state of painful uneasiness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Eager desire.</def> <rj><au>J. D.
Forbes</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A state of restlessness and
agitation, often with general indisposition and a distressing sense of
oppression at the epigastrium.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Care; solicitude; foreboding; uneasiness;
perplexity; disquietude; disquiet; trouble; apprehension; restlessness.
See <er>Care</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 67 --></p>

<p><ent>Anxious</ent>⟦br⟧
